  "format": "Sean, Amanda, and Van review Benny Safdie's 'The Smashing Machine,' then Sean and Amanda rebuild the Best Picture top 10, and Sean talks to Safdie.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘The Smashing Machine’",
      "note": "with Van Lathan",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "The Smashing Machine",
          "year": 2025,
          "note": "Safdie recreates much of the Mark Kerr documentary and keeps the camera outside the ring. Van and Sean read it as a spiritual sequel to The Curse: surveillance-style, alienated, with Dwayne Johnson dropping the wrestler persona to play a soft-spoken fighter. Amanda thinks the approach is undercut by an underwritten, one-note Emily Blunt role."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "ranking",
      "heading": "Best Picture Power Rankings",
